## Documentation

For comprehensive documentation, visit [docs.konnektr.io/docs/db-query-operator](https://docs.konnektr.io/docs/db-query-operator)

## Quick Start

Install the operator:

```bash
helm install db-query-operator \
  oci://ghcr.io/konnektr-io/charts/{{ template "chart.name" . }} \
  --version {{ template "chart.version" . }} \
  --namespace dbqo-system \
  --create-namespace \
  --set gvkPattern="v1/ConfigMap;apps/v1/Deployment"
```

## Prerequisites

- Kubernetes 1.24+
- Helm 3.8+
- PostgreSQL database accessible from the cluster

## Configuration

The `gvkPattern` parameter is required and specifies which Kubernetes resource types the operator can manage.

### Format

`<group>/<version>/<Kind>` or `<version>/<Kind>` for core resources

### Examples

```bash
# Core resources
--set gvkPattern="v1/ConfigMap;v1/Secret;v1/Service"

# Applications
--set gvkPattern="apps/v1/Deployment;apps/v1/StatefulSet"

# ArgoCD Applications
--set gvkPattern="argoproj.io/v1alpha1/Application"

# Multiple types
--set gvkPattern="v1/ConfigMap;apps/v1/Deployment;argoproj.io/v1alpha1/Application"
```

